{"batch":"Cross-cutting Sweep","batch_index":3,"assessments":{"error_consistency":73.0},"dimension_notes":{"error_consistency":{"evidence":["`goseg/routines/version.go` has public wrappers (`StartVersionSubsystem`, `CheckVersionLoop`) that explicitly discard errors from their `WithContext` variants via `_ = ...`, while sibling orchestration code generally returns/propagates errors.","`goseg/main.go` `startDevMode` launches `http.ListenAndServe` in a goroutine without handling its returned error, creating another fire-and-forget failure path.","`goseg/docker/network/network.go` `killContainerUsingPortWithRuntime` returns raw `DockerClientNewFn` errors (`return err`) while most neighboring functions wrap with operation context.","`goseg/system/disk.go` `CreateGroundSegFilesystem` forwards several nested errors without adding step context (`return \"\", err`), unlike other functions in the same file that wrap failures.","`goseg/rectify/rectify.go` and `goseg/docker/orchestration/subsystem/docker.go` consume channels without closure checks (`event := <-ch`, `event := <-messages`, `err := <-errs`), so closed channels can degrade into silent zero-value handling/looping instead of explicit terminal errors."],"impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","confidence":"high"}},"findings":[{"dimension":"error_consistency","identifier":"discarded_background_errors","summary":"Non-context entrypoints suppress background subsystem failures instead of surfacing them consistently.","related_files":["goseg/routines/version.go","goseg/main.go"],"evidence":["`StartVersionSubsystem()` and `CheckVersionLoop()` use `_ = ...WithContext(...)`, dropping terminal errors from version/update loops.","`startDevMode()` runs `go http.ListenAndServe(\"0.0.0.0:6060\", nil)` and ignores returned listener errors entirely."],"suggestion":"Standardize launcher behavior: either return errors to callers or report through a shared error channel/logger callback with structured context; avoid `_ =` on fallible subsystem startups.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"async_error_sinkholes"},{"dimension":"error_consistency","identifier":"missing_error_context_on_propagation","summary":"Some boundary functions return raw nested errors, making failure provenance inconsistent across modules.","related_files":["goseg/docker/network/network.go","goseg/system/disk.go","goseg/startup_orchestrator.go"],"evidence":["`killContainerUsingPortWithRuntime` returns raw client-construction error (`return err`) while other network functions wrap with operation context.","`CreateGroundSegFilesystem` returns raw errors from `nextGroundSegPath`, `formatGroundSegFilesystem`, and `reconcileGroundSegFstab` without annotating step/context.","`syncRetrieveWithStartram` returns upstream error directly (`return err`) despite surrounding startup code typically wrapping failures with subsystem labels."],"suggestion":"Adopt a consistent boundary rule: wrap propagated errors at module/service boundaries with operation-specific context using `%w`, and reserve raw propagation for tightly scoped helper internals only.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"module","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"context_loss_on_boundary"},{"dimension":"error_consistency","identifier":"channel_closure_not_treated_as_error_boundary","summary":"Multiple long-running loops read channels without closure checks, so producer shutdown is not handled as an explicit failure mode.","related_files":["goseg/rectify/rectify.go","goseg/docker/orchestration/subsystem/docker.go"],"evidence":["`runTransitionEventLoop` uses `case event := <-ch` with no `ok` check; closed channels can repeatedly deliver zero values and bypass explicit termination/error reporting.","`dockerListenerWithContext` reads `event := <-messages` and `err := <-errs` without `ok`; when channels close, logic falls into nil/zero-value paths (`continue` on nil err) instead of deterministic shutdown error semantics."],"suggestion":"Use two-value receives (`v, ok := <-ch`) in long-lived loops; treat `!ok` as a terminal boundary and either return a wrapped error or exit explicitly with a clear reason.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"async_error_sinkholes"}],"retrospective":{"root_causes":["Async subsystem APIs mix fire-and-forget and error-returning patterns without a single contract for operational failures.","Boundary-wrapping policy is inconsistent, so some call paths lose actionable context when propagating errors.","Channel lifecycle handling is under-specified in event loops, leading to implicit instead of explicit failure boundaries."],"likely_symptoms":["discarded_background_errors","channel_closure_not_treated_as_error_boundary"],"possible_false_positives":[]}}


